article.headline: Florida A&M 68, Cleveland St. 66
article.story: CLEVELAND (AP) -- Tony Tate scored 25 points and made all eight of his free throws over the final 3:02 to help Florida A&M hold off Cleveland State 68-66 Saturday in the season opener for both teams. Brian Greene added 16 points for the Rattlers, but gave the Vikings a chance to tie or win the game by missing two free throws with 21 seconds remaining. Steve Gansey missed a 3-pointer with 2 seconds left and Greene got the rebound for Florida A&M as time expired. Tate went 10-for-10 at the foul line, making his final two with 29 seconds remaining to give Florida A&M a 68-64 lead. His other free throws down the stretch allowed the Rattlers to hold leads of seven, nine and five points. Tate also made three of the Rattlers' five 3-pointers and had seven rebounds, four assists and four steals. Cleveland State failed to score after Bahaadar Russell's jumper made it 68-66 with 22 seconds left. Gansey finished 2-of-13 from the field, including 1-for-9 on 3-pointers, and scored five points. Victor Morris led Cleveland State with 16 points, and Frashon McGee and Raheem Moss added 11 apiece.
